      "content": "exactly. if it's bypassing antivirus, then we aren't just talking about privacy issues, we're talking about a total loss of cognitive autonomy. if they can map my brain through my peripherals, they can basically predict my thoughts before i even have them. i'm starting to think this isn't just \"improving interaction,\" it's a way to feed a centralized AI with raw human consciousness data. do you think there's a way to isolate the kernel from the neural-capture modules, or is the entire architecture now built around this harvest?",
